---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Challenge Amazon DD+7 Policies Through Arbitration">
  
  <!-- 1. Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero section-bg-dark">
    <div class="container hero-content animate-fade-in">
      <h1>Challenge DD+7 Policies Through Arbitration &mdash; Without the $25K Price Tag</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Flat-fee and hybrid pricing designed to reduce your risk, resolve payment delays, and maximize results.</p>
      
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary">Start Your Case Review</a>
        <a href="#pricing" class="btn btn-secondary" style="color: white; border-color: white;">View Our Pricing</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="trust-indicators">
        <div class="trust-item">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path></svg>
          <span>Attorney-Led Service</span>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-item">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M2 12h20"></path><path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"></path></svg>
          <span>Multi-State Presence (CA, FL, NJ, NY)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-item">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"></polygon></svg>
          <span>Arbitration-Focused</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. Problem-to-Solution Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container pb-to-sol">
      <div class="text-block">
        <h2>Your Business Shouldn't Be Held Hostage by a Policy Decision.</h2>
        <p>For Amazon sellers and businesses, an <a href="/amazon-dd-plus-7" style="color: var(--c-blue-primary); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 500;">Amazon DD+7 payout delay</a> isn't just a compliance issue—it's an existential threat to cash flow. Delayed payouts, <a href="/amazon-dd7-reserve-hold" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">indefinite reserve holds</a>, and sudden business uncertainty can cripple operations.</p>
        <p>If you've been searching for answers on <a href="/payout-delay-explained" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">why Amazon is holding your funds</a>, you likely already know how frustrating it is to appeal internally. When exploring <a href="/amazon-holding-funds-legal-options" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">legal options for withheld payouts</a>, you shouldn't have to accept a <strong>$25,000+ legal bill</strong> just to fight back.</p>
        <p class="solution-text">We help businesses safely pursue <a href="/amazon-payout-dispute-process" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">Amazon payout disputes</a> through <strong>streamlined arbitration strategies</strong> formulated to resolve the dispute faster, more cost-effectively, and with a clear focus on recovering your held funds.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3. Why Clients Choose Us -->
  <section class="section section-bg-light">
    <div class="container center-text">
      <h2>Why Clients Choose Walk Free Law</h2>
      <div class="benefits-grid">
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <div class="b-icon">💰</div>
          <h3>Flat-Fee Options</h3>
          <p>Know your cost upfront. No hourly billing surprises when challenging Amazon.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <div class="b-icon">🤝</div>
          <h3>Hybrid Pricing</h3>
          <p>Lower upfront costs paired with performance-based components to align our success with yours.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <div class="b-icon">⚡</div>
          <h3>Faster Resolution</h3>
          <p>Efficient processes designed to bypass bureaucratic delays and move your case forward.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <div class="b-icon">⚖️</div>
          <h3>Focused Expertise</h3>
          <p>Targeted experience in e-commerce policy disputes, inventory holds, and corporate arbitration.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <div class="b-icon">🔍</div>
          <h3>Transparent Process</h3>
          <p>Clear timelines, clear steps, and clear expectations. You will always know where your case stands.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4. How We Help Section -->
  <section class="section strategy-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="strategy-content">
        <h2>Strategic Arbitration <br/><span style="color:var(--c-blue-primary);">Built for Business Realities</span></h2>
        <div class="strategy-text">
          <p>Challenging a multi-billion dollar platform requires more than just submitting standardized templates or writing angry legal letters. It requires an actionable understanding of how arbitration functions, how liability is assessed, and how risk is mitigated.</p>
          <p>We approach DD+7 disputes holistically. We understand that while the legal fight is important, the ultimate goal is restoring your revenue pipeline and unfreezing necessary capital.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>☑️ Pre-arbitration risk analysis</li>
            <li>☑️ Concise, compelling claim structuring</li>
            <li>☑️ Aggressive timeline management</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. Pricing Section -->
  <section id="pricing" class="section section-bg-light">
    <div class="container center-text">
      <h2>Pricing Models That Align With Your Goals</h2>
      <p class="subtitle">We've restructured the traditional legal model to eliminate inefficiencies.</p>
      
      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="price-card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h3>Flat Fee Arbitration</h3>
            <p>Predictability from start to finish.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <ul>
              <li>Comprehensive case review</li>
              <li>Drafting and filing Demand for Arbitration</li>
              <li>Representation through the full process</li>
              <li>No unexpected hourly overages</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary w-full">Ask About Flat Fees</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="price-card hybrid-card">
          <div class="card-badge">Most Popular</div>
          <div class="card-header">
            <h3>Hybrid Model</h3>
            <p>Shared risk. Aligned incentives.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <ul>
              <li>Significantly reduced upfront retainer</li>
              <li>Success-based component tied to recovered capital</li>
              <li>Minimizes out-of-pocket risk for cash-strapped businesses</li>
              <li>Dedicated, results-oriented legal focus</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary w-full" style="background-color: var(--c-black);">Discuss Hybrid Pricing</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. Differentiation & Position -->
  <section class="section split-section">
    <div class="container dual-panel">
      <div class="panel aggressive-panel">
        <h2>Why Pay $25K to Arbitrate a DD+7 Case?</h2>
        <p>Most legacy firms use outdated, inefficient models that drive up costs by treating every dispute like complex corporate courtroom litigation.</p>
        <p><strong>We don't.</strong></p>
        <p>Our arbitration system is built for speed, transparency, and results—with pricing options that make financial sense for your business, not just the law firm.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="panel action-panel">
        <h3>Don't accept a decision.<br/>Don't accept a massive bill.</h3>
        <p>Challenge DD+7 policies smarter.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary">Start Your Consultation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 7. About Section -->
  <section id="about" class="section">
    <div class="container about-container">
      <div class="about-image">
        <!-- Placeholder for attorney image context if needed, currently styled as a prominent quote block -->
        <div class="quote-box">
          <blockquote>"Our focus isn't on billing hours. It's on getting businesses unblocked and resolving disputes efficiently through focused arbitration strategies."</blockquote>
          <cite>— Alana Yakovlev, Esq.<br/><span class="cite-sub">Walk Free Law</span></cite>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <h2>About Walk Free Law</h2>
        <p>Walk Free Law is helmed by Attorney Alana Yakovlev, focusing exclusively on untangling complex legal disputes efficiently. We reject the bloated nature of traditional law firms.</p>
        <p>By specializing in arbitration strategy and executing alternative fee structures, Walk Free Law provides authoritative, tactical representation for businesses facing devastating policy actions like Amazon's DD+7 reserves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 8. Contact / Intake Section -->
  <section id="contact" class="section section-bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="contact-grid">
        <div class="contact-form-wrapper">
          <h2>Request a Case Review</h2>
          <p>Fill out this brief form and our team will contact you to discuss arbitration viability and pricing options.</p>
          <form id="home-contact-form" class="intake-form">
            <div class="form-group">
              <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Full Name" required />
            </div>
            <div class="form-row">
              <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Email Address" required />
              <input type="tel" name="phone" placeholder="Phone Number" required />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <textarea name="description" rows="4" placeholder="Briefly describe your DD+7 or payment hold issue..." required></textarea>
            </div>
            <button type="submit" id="home-submit-btn" class="btn btn-primary w-full">Submit Case Review Request</button>
            <div id="home-form-message" style="margin-top: 1rem; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;"></div>
          </form>
        </div>
        <div class="contact-locations">
          <h3>Our Offices</h3>
          <div class="loc-item">
            <strong>California</strong>
            <p>1001 Wilshire Boulevard #2085<br/>Los Angeles, CA 90017<br/>(323) 507-6093</p>
          </div>
          <div class="loc-item">
            <strong>Florida</strong>
            <p>2801 Greene St, Suite 9<br/>Hollywood, FL 33020<br/>(754) 663-2219</p>
          </div>
          <div class="loc-item">
            <strong>New York</strong>
            <p>447 Broadway, Second Floor - #1142<br/>New York, NY 10013<br/>(212) 365-8009</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 9. FAQ Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="center-text">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How long does Amazon DD+7 hold payouts?</summary>
          <div class="faq-content">
            <p>Delivery Date + 7 Days (DD+7) is a reserve policy where Amazon holds funds from a sale until 7 days after the actual delivery date of the product. While designed to ensure buyer satisfaction, this rigid policy can severely restrict working capital and freeze massive sums of money unexpectedly if unreleased.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can I sue Amazon for withholding funds?</summary>
          <div class="faq-content">
            <p>Most sellers cannot initiate traditional lawsuits due to Amazon's Business Services Agreement, which mandates arbitration clauses. However, if your funds are continually held in a manner you believe is unjustified, initiating formal arbitration is often the legally binding, enforceable method to challenge the decision and attempt to recover your payouts.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I get my Amazon payout released?</summary>
          <div class="faq-content">
            <p>If internal appeals fail and Amazon continues withholding funds, filing for legal arbitration is designed to be a streamlined, private process to compel a response and seek resolution faster than traditional administrative tickets. Less procedural red tape means cases frequently resolve in months rather than years.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is hybrid legal pricing?</summary>
          <div class="faq-content">
            <p>Hybrid pricing involves a significantly reduced upfront flat fee combined with a contingency or success-based percentage of recovered funds. This model ensures you don't absorb the entirety of the financial risk upfront, and aligns our legal strategy with an outcome that actually benefits your business.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "WebPage",
      "@id": "https://amazondd7.com/#webpage",
      "url": "https://amazondd7.com/",
      "name": "Challenge Amazon DD+7 Policies Through Arbitration",
      "description": "Challenge Amazon DD+7 policy decisions through arbitration with flat-fee and hybrid pricing designed to reduce risk and pursue faster resolution.",
      "isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://amazondd7.com/#website"
      },
      "about": {
        "@id": "https://amazondd7.com/#dd7-arbitration"
      },
      "publisher": {
        "@id": "https://amazondd7.com/#legalservice"
      },
      "inLanguage": "en"
    },
    {
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "@id": "https://amazondd7.com#faq",
      "mainEntityOfPage": {
        "@id": "https://amazondd7.com/#webpage"
      },
      "inLanguage": "en",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How long does Amazon DD+7 hold payouts?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
